    <li><h1>Postdocs</h1>
    NOW HIRING!  <blockquote>POSTDOCTORAL POSITION IN EXPERIMENTAL NEUTRINO PHYSICS
Department of Physics and CERCA
Case Western Reserve University
<p>
The experimental neutrino group at Case Western Reserve University is looking for a postdoctoral associate in experimental neutrino physics, with an emphasis on the Project 8 experiment.  Project 8 is an international effort to measure the neutrino mass by doing high-precision spectroscopy of tritium using radiofrequency and atomic physics methods.  In addition to Project 8, the group also works on low-energy neutrino and dark matter detection projects.  
<p>

Experience in particle astrophysics, nuclear physics, or closely related fields is helpful, but we'll consider applicants with relevant atomic/molecular/optical or experimental astronomy/CMB instrumentation backgrounds.   The position is available immediately.
<p>

Please send a cover letter, CV, statement of research interests, and contact information for three references to Prof. Ben Monreal via the address neutrino-postdoc-search@case.edu.  The position remains open until filled.   

</blockquote>

